    "created_at": "2013-06-24T18:59:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-06-24T19:00:27Z",
    "body": "Where were you imagining the env would load `RUST_TEST_TASKS` instead of `RUST_THREADS`? It'd be simple enough to also check `getenv(RUST_TEST_TASKS)` and use that if it exists (at https://github.com/mozilla/rust/blob/master/src/rt/rust_env.cpp#L87) but it seems a bit messy to include test logic in the main env loader. \n\nUnless I'm mistaken, the result of that environmental setting gets loaded for both tests and non-tests when creating the scheduler at https://github.com/mozilla/rust/blob/master/src/rt/rust_kernel.cpp#L49 so not sure if there is a cleaner place to add in the test-specific env stuff, or if it belongs in `src/rt/rust_env.cpp`?\n",
